## Golden Rules (Non-Negotiable)

### DO
- **Imports at TOP of file** — No inline imports, ever
- **Config in dedicated files** — Use environment variables and config classes
- **Keep it simple** — Write the minimal code that solves the problem
- **Documentation explains WHY** — Not what the code does
- **Every line is maintenance** — Code you write is code you maintain

### DON'T
- Raw SQL in application code (use stored procedures or an abstraction layer)
- Business logic in UI components
- Walls of text in documentation
- Unnecessary error handling wrappers (don't try-catch everything)
- Repeat business logic — follow the DRY principle
- Over-engineer or add "future-proofing" that isn't needed

