## Testing Standards

> **Philosophy:** "Test every code path. 2 branches = 2 tests. State coverage over line coverage."

### Test Types

| Type | Purpose | Speed | Mocking |
|------|---------|-------|---------|
| **Unit** | Test isolated logic | Fast (<100ms) | Mock dependencies |
| **Integration** | Test system interactions | Slower | Real database (Docker) |
| **E2E** | Test user workflows | Slowest | Real everything |

### Test File Location
| Source File | Test File |
|-------------|-----------|
| `src/services/user_service.py` | `tests/unit/services/test_user_service.py` |
| `src/hooks/useUser.ts` | `src/hooks/__tests__/useUser.test.ts` |
| Feature integration | `tests/integration/test_user_flow.py` |

### Test Naming Convention
```
test_{function}_{scenario}_{expected_outcome}
```

**Examples:**
- `test_create_user_valid_input_returns_user_id`
- `test_create_user_duplicate_email_raises_conflict_error`
- `test_create_user_empty_name_raises_validation_error`

### Backend Unit Test Template
```python
import pytest
from unittest.mock import Mock, AsyncMock

@pytest.mark.asyncio
async def test_create_user_valid_input_returns_user():
    # Arrange
    mock_databridge = Mock()
    mock_databridge.create_user = AsyncMock(
        return_value=User(id=1, email="test@example.com", name="Test")
    )
    service = UserService(mock_databridge)
    request = UserRequest(email="test@example.com", name="Test")
    
    # Act
    result = await service.create_user(request)
    
    # Assert
    assert result.id == 1
    assert result.email == "test@example.com"
    mock_databridge.create_user.assert_called_once_with(request)


@pytest.mark.asyncio
async def test_create_user_duplicate_email_raises_error():
    # Arrange
    mock_databridge = Mock()
    mock_databridge.email_exists = AsyncMock(return_value=True)
    service = UserService(mock_databridge)
    
    # Act & Assert
    with pytest.raises(DuplicateEmailError):
        await service.create_user(UserRequest(email="exists@example.com", name="Test"))
```

### Frontend Hook Test Template
```typescript
import { renderHook, waitFor, act } from '@testing-library/react';
import { useUser } from '../useUser';
import * as userApi from '~/api/userApi';

jest.mock('~/api/userApi');

describe('useUser', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    jest.clearAllMocks();
  });

  it('returns user data on successful create', async () => {
    // Arrange
    const mockUser = { id: 1, email: 'test@example.com', name: 'Test' };
    (userApi.createUser as jest.Mock).mockResolvedValue(mockUser);
    
    // Act
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useUser());
    
    await act(async () => {
      await result.current.create({ email: 'test@example.com', name: 'Test' });
    });
    
    // Assert
    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(result.current.data).toEqual(mockUser);
      expect(result.current.isLoading).toBe(false);
      expect(result.current.error).toBeNull();
    });
  });

  it('sets error state on API failure', async () => {
    // Arrange
    (userApi.createUser as jest.Mock).mockRejectedValue(new Error('Network error'));
    
    // Act
    const { result } = renderHook(() => useUser());
    
    await act(async () => {
      await result.current.create({ email: 'test@example.com', name: 'Test' });
    });
    
    // Assert
    await waitFor(() => {
      expect(result.current.error).toBe('Network error');
      expect(result.current.data).toBeNull();
    });
  });
});
```

### Test Quality Checklist
- [ ] Each test tests ONE thing
- [ ] Test names describe scenario and expected outcome
- [ ] No copy-paste test code (use fixtures/factories)
- [ ] No business logic reimplemented in tests
- [ ] Assertions check outcomes, not implementation details
- [ ] Unit tests are fast

### What to Test

| Layer | What to Test | What NOT to Test |
|-------|--------------|------------------|
| **Service** | Business logic, edge cases, error handling | Framework behavior |
| **Databridge** | Query mapping, error translation | Database engine |
| **Hook** | State transitions, loading/error states | React internals |
| **Component** | Rendering, user interactions | CSS styling |

