## Development Workflow

### Before Writing Code
1. **Search** the codebase for similar patterns
2. **Draft interfaces** (data contracts) first
3. **Implement** minimal logic — simplest solution
4. **Validate** — try to break your own code
5. **Test** — write tests and run them

### Feature Development Flow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Requirements] --> B{Clear?}
    B -->|No| C[Ask Questions]
    C --> A
    B -->|Yes| D[Design/Blueprint]
    D --> E{Approved?}
    E -->|No| D
    E -->|Yes| F[Implement]
    F --> G[Test]
    G --> H{Pass?}
    H -->|No| F
    H -->|Yes| I[Review]
```

### Build Order (Backend)
1. **Database** — Stored procedures/migrations
2. **Models** — Pydantic request/response models
3. **Databridge** — Data access layer
4. **Service** — Business logic
5. **Router** — HTTP endpoints
6. **Tests** — Unit and integration

### Build Order (Frontend)
1. **Models** — TypeScript interfaces
2. **API** — HTTP client functions
3. **Hooks** — State and logic
4. **Components** — UI elements
5. **Pages** — Route compositions
6. **Tests** — Unit tests and stories (tests should be easy to write, or you just write bad code)

